      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c69797b70e2d8d6f",
      "text": "If [[the future machine]] is to be a new kind of computer as an adaptive, self-referential thinking machine, whose logic and program nevertheless originate from human beings, then, as Günther makes clear, the thinking, the consciousness and ultimately also the ethics of these human beings are part of the program of the machine that executes it. The future machine and the ethics of its designers are thus inseparable."
    },
